Class ParserNodesNumberException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • services.xml.exception.ParserException
          • services.xml.exception.ParserSyntaxException

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParserBoundedNodesNumberException, ParserLowerBoundedNodesNumberException

    public abstract class ParserNodesNumberException
extends ParserSyntaxException
    This type of exception is thrown when the number of nodes of one type is invalid. For example, no delivery address in a delivery request.
